	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I assume you meant &quot;unlike the NES&quot;? (the original GB only had a single palette for all the background, period)</div><br /><br />No, I meant what I said. The GBC BG tiles could have their palettes set on a per-tile basis, hence GBC BG tiles <em>are unlike</em> DMG BG tiles, which had a system-wide palette. The GBC has no concept of a single palette that will be used by all BG tiles; the closest you get is Palette #0 being the default in VRAM since everything in the BG Tile Attributes is initially empty.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


