	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Macbee wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm trying to create different patterns and so far only horizontal dithering doesn't look deformed on AV/NTSC:<br /></div>For whatever it's worth, three 2A03 pixels make two NTSC color periods, and the 2A03 chroma phase shift repeats every 3 scanlines, so if you use a dithering pattern that's a multiple of three pixels wide (and three high), it will compensate as best as possible for that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
